a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Young, full of hate, a formless arm of Innoruuk appears.</span><hr size=1> Darkrayne led the naieve child away from the dim streets of Neriak into the world of Norrath. Natori  had not been around much at all, she had seen no more of Norrath then the city gates. Outside, Darkrayne tried to explain everything to Natori, leaving out a great many detail. All the ambassador's daughter understood was she was no longer going to be living a life of luxury. Something she found apalling.<br>
<br>
Being the Ambassador's only child, she was spoilt to every degree you could think of. Natori put this treatment to use almost immediately. Refusing everything Dark asked of her, Darkrayne almost had to literally drag her any further.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am going to teach you the law of the land. But before we do that, your first lesson will be trust. You have none but your sword and me to trust. You will do so implicitly, and your rewards shall be plenty. Should you disobey, my punishment is strict.&quot; <br>
<br>
Darkrayne managed to get Natori into the basic fencing stance that all nobility was taught growing up. From there he unbelted his Morning star and challenged Natori to a Duel. She did not wish to accept, but Darkrayne tricked her into one anyway. His morning star crashed down but the agile girl easily stepped aside. She countered his strike but with the force of her blow, and Darkrayne's armor, the results were ineffective. Darkrayne stepped back and quickly released a spell, Natori's feet were stuck to the ground, she cried out &quot;What witchery is this?!&quot; just before receiving a blast of force to her chest. Natori dropped to one knee and passed out. <br>
<br>
When she came to, Darkrayne told her. &quot;Disobey my word even slightly and so shall be your punishment. Following my direction and every word i speak, this will be your reward&quot;<br>
<br>
Darkrayne reached into his pack and pulled out a Leather Tunic made of Tsech Mas Gnoll hide and instructed Natori to put it on, turning his back to let her change.<br>
<br>
Many a lesson went on like this, but Dark needn't punish Natori more then that one time. Next, Dark told her of the second lesson, &quot;only the stronger ones survive, you are a survivor, everyone around you is weak. Trust no one but yourself and your sword, and myself of course; do NOT show emotion before your enemy, for they will use it against you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Natori took those words to heart.<br>
<br>
The next day, Darkrayne explored Nektulous while the Young warrior slept in (It was during this time that Darkrayne had an encounter with a Teir'Dal that tried to denounce the Father in front of a devout servant). Slaying two more Halflings, Darkrayne had the necessary materials to complete his Quest of Culling, this was day 2 since being given his quest, but try as he did, he could not get ahold of the Dread Overlord who originated his quest.<br>
<br>
Dark returned to where he and Natori slept the night, she had been up and got lost exploring the more unfamiliar parts of the city. Darkrayne chided the girl on her adventure and warned that the underground, the ones that poisoned her father, still sought after both of them. <br>
<br>
Many days passed, Natori grew in strength and in mind. Learning the immediate areas of Nektulous  now, Dark took leave of her to journey further out of the forest then he had ever done by himself. Before leaving he rewarded Natori with a few gifts of armor and a weapon better then the rusty blade she had and he warned her of the beings clad in black, sporting the scarlet glowing golden crown, and if she were to see even one of these men, to find the nearest source of cover and hide herself until they passed. With that, Darkrayne left for the Eastern commonlands, it was here he first interacted with lighties in an alliance against the despicable orcs of Clan Deathfist...many an orc fell to his morning star, many a battle wound he received, and many a circle of trials he passed through.<br>
<br>
More to Come... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/udarkrayne2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkrayne2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/02 5:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Young, full of hate, a formless arm of Innoruuk appears.</span><hr size=1> A loud thunderclap, and the tiny spattering of raindrops on the ground. <br>
<br>
&quot;BLAST it...that old fart has done it to me AGAIN!&quot; <br>
Darkrayne shouted aloud to no one important. Pausing a moment only to look around. No one was near or heard him make a fool of himself.  Another step, another curse under his breath to the god Karana. Anger rising inside, he sought the nearest creature and took out his rage on it's carcass. One less Kodiak to bother him ever again. <br>
<br>
&quot;What are you staring at? BEGONE before I feel energy enough to slay you next. This is your only chance&quot; <br>
<br>
Darkrayne spoke to a Koada'Dal that seemed to appear out of nowhere, sobbing and mourning for the dumb beast that lay in a heap at his feet.<br>
 <br>
After another look, Dark's features softened a little. This was just a child. Though Hate drives Darkrayne, he has an unusual soft streak in him from time to time. Very unusual for a Teir'Dal. A high-pitched voice, broken up by loud sobs lilted to his ear. &quot;Why *sniff* did you d-do that?&quot; The child broke out in louds sniffles and sobs again. Darkrayne said nothing. <br>
&quot;Sh-she was m-my friend&quot; the Koada'Dal said. Surveying the area around, Dark noted that ther was none other then him and the Wood Elf, Darkrayne chose, instead of looking foolish, to do something. He sat a moment, closed his eyes, bringing memory of a spell he just recently learned to the front. Dark stood up and, looking around one last time - coast was clear - Darkrayne began to cast his Reanimation spell. Seeing the child joyful again he turned to go without a word. Before getting another step he felt something tugging at the tail of his robe. The young elf was gripping him tight. &quot;Egha...wha? Get off me you filthy thing. Go play with your friend before I decide to kill it again.&quot; Dark shook the child off and mumbled some unpriestly words under his breath. As he continued on his journey to Kithicore woods, he heard the faint child's voice calling him a big meanie and then shortly thereafter laughter.<br>
<br>
&quot;Foolishness...and what in all the hells compelled me to do that for her?&quot; Was all Dark could think of.<br>
<br>
During the night, Dark was rudely awoken. He was being grabbed and held tight. A Voice spoke to him in bad Teir'Dal<br>
&quot;Oi got ya now priest. Da boss is gunna reward me guud.&quot;<br>
A Large Ogre sporting the Glowing Crown on his Black vestplate quickly dropped Darkrayne's morale. Dark made a futile attempt to struggle against the oaf but he was no where near strong enough to escape. All Dark could do was piss the big one off, and he paid for that. A Sharp stinging pain, followed by a numbing sensation quickly spread over Dark's body going from head to his toe. Before losing consciousness, Dark could feel something warm ooze down his neck...then all was black.<br>
<br>
<br>
