<br>
No, Darkrayne's biggest problems were the pounding migraine he had, and a blasted itch in the middle of his shoulderblades on his back.<br>
<br>
Groggily shaking his head he looked about, vision blurry from the blunt force to his head. Nothing, nothing at all could be determined. Nothing except that he was hanging from a pair of shackles attached to a wall.  A quiet dripping sound pounded with the force of a bull in Darkrayne's ear. The stench of blood mingled with tears and some combustible acidic scent nearly made the priest vomit. He had smelled worse though, Ogres aren't the cleanliest things in Norrath, that's a given.<br>
<br>
Time passed what seemed an eternity. Darkrayne's arms were going numb from lack of blood flow. He himself was thirsty and tired and weak both physically and mentally. Then he heard footsteps, 3 pair...or so he thought. A loud creak of a rusty-hinged door and deep voices, that of a Human and a couple that he could not make out. &quot;Damnable Human scum, I should wish to be captured by these imbecillic and blind wastes of goo and flesh.&quot; The Human, clad in Ravenscale with a Bright crown emblazoned on his chest which he wore proud stared at the priest a moment. He spoke in Fluent Teir'Dal<br>
&quot;So, mister...holy man. What are you to do....mmm mmm mm, such a shame...your gear however will turn quite the coin in the black market, I thank you for your donation.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Human paused a moment. Dark said nothing and the Human got indignant. 'I should say! USUALLY one replies to a thank you, it is just rude not to!.&quot; Darkrayne summoned enough strength to look up at the man in the eyes. <br>
He was a fairly charismatic example of his species, Brown hair, light blue eyes and a healthy body.  He would be a difficult one to kill, even with more experience. &quot;Well?!&quot; Dark's thoughts were interrupted by the Human again. &quot;SPEAK!&quot; the human said. Darkrayne tried to retort with some of his smart-ass wit but his voice was sore, hoarse and dry, he couldn't even whisper so he just stared. The Human then smacked Darkrayne a heavy blow with the back of his hand. Dark's cracked lips split open and bled. After recovering from the shock he turned his head back to the Human and smiled an evil smile, licking the blood and just staring blankly.<br>
&quot;Cut this worthless lump of waste down and give  him a bit of water to loosen his tongue, if he doesn't speak it, he will die instead.&quot; The Human spun on his heel and left the room.<br>
One of the Guards then proceeded to do as he was told, taking a Dirk that was obviously looted from one of Neriak's Dragoons and cutting through Darkrayne's shackles which were made of linen and bit deep into his flesh.<br>
<br>
Upon landing Darkrayne's knees buckled under him and he crumpled. The guard gave him a swift boot and grabbed him by the nape of his neck. &quot;You filthy blue punks.&quot; The Human said in not near as perfect Teir'Dal as the first man did.<br>
&quot;You are a waste of my time elf.&quot; the guard said driving his dirk deep into Darkrayne's shoulder and cuffing him upside the head before pulling him with. The other guard just stood and watched, helping when necessary. <br>
<br>
<br>
Is all the time i have, more to come soon though.<br>
