 Rugs from Erudin, bows from Kelethin, even a scythe, and the hand of the previous Teir'Dal owner. &quot;Do come in my friend, you and I have plenty to speak about and I amnot one to waste time.&quot; The Human spoke to Dark in his native tongue.<br>
Darkrayne collapsed in a coushined sofa and stared a hole through the Human.<br>
 &quot;Now then Teir'Dal, you have some information that I did not like for you to have gotten ahold of, you have killed a couple of my agents though young and foolish they were. Most of all, you interrupted my plans, and THAT I cannot forgive you for.<br>
The deal is simple. You join my cause, and I shall keep you alive. You will still be able to worship your silly deity, but you will have an additional responsibility to me and my orders. Now, considering the incredible cost and expense you have given me, AND the half year setback at LEAST, my offer is FAR more then fair. What say you?&quot; The Human was true to his word, he did not waste time at all. <br>
&quot;Why do you wish me to join when before you were to kill me?&quot;<br>
Darkrayne asked. &quot;You are a priest no? As of late, my priest has had to..um...meet his Goddess, and she did not find favor in him&quot; The human shook his head and laughed as he indicated the head of a Feir'Dal Cleric spiked outside this building as a symbol to all that would speak up against his cause.<br>
Darkrayne grinned evilly, perhaps this Human had the prospects of being a very good ally to him and to the guild he was trying to be part of. &quot;You show me one head of a weak lighty and expect me to be frightened into your ranks? You underestimate me Human.&quot; Darkrayne said. The Human responded, &quot;So do I now? We shall see about that, because the more trouble you give me, the more your abilities will be needed as I remove limbs from your body one by one. Now, let us move on, give me a name.&quot; The Human said, &quot;Innoruuk&quot; the priest responded. &quot;Ouch...wrong answer Dark Elf.&quot; The Human nodded to his guard. The one that stabbed him earlier came over and took his dirk (the same that left a wound in Dark's shoulder) grabbing Dark's hand he asked in broken Teir'Dal &quot;Which finger you lose?&quot;  Ignoring the guard Dark began to recite a spell in his  mind. &quot;So be it&quot; the guard said, placing Dark's index finger out. Just before he removed the limb, Dark released his spell, the guard was knocked onto his back and dazed of sorts. Grinning, Darkrayne spoke in his tongue &quot;Innoruuk sends you his greetings.&quot; and released a 2nd smite spell. The guard cried out in pain before blacking out. Not another second before the 2nd guard was on Darkrayne, he did not waste time with which extremity to remove, he just swung his halberd with deadly force. Darkrayne unleashed a quick spell that stunned the guard, before he threw his smite. Backing into a corner in a defensive position he rooted the guard and smote him to death. <br>
After the second guard was down, the Human stood up.<br>
&quot;Are you finished? Or do I have to get more? Perhaps you'd rather fight me instead since you seem to have strength left in you.&quot; Darkrayne knew his mind was fatigued, he didn't have enough strength to muster another spell for a good couple minutes. &quot;I am finished&quot; Dark said in Teir'Dal.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good, you have wasted 3 minutes of my time priest. And I am not pleased.&quot; Darkrayne was struck by a force of wind that took his breath from him. &quot;Now, give me YOUR name or die&quot; the human said, a ring of flames surrounding his fists.<br>
&quot;I..am...Drinseth G'Naltha...student of the great Rayneth Sithren&quot; Dark scowled at the Human. His hate causing strength to surface from the depths of his body. No one knew his name, for it was a Drinseth that killed the Feir'Dal prophet.<br>
<br>
