<br>
Dark was now well known in Highpass, he had gained a reputation of his deeds and no longer would the guards treat him like a common orc, or a lowly Ogre.<br>
<br>
Dark, though his hatred for the followers of the followers of light was quite evident, grew accustomed to working with them in a common cause. Choosing to just sit back and keep quiet, Darkrayne survived his encounters, curing any battle wounds the warriors took. He knew full well if he were to open his mouth only unpriestly things would come out. <br>
<br>
Tolerance was his biggest ally in these slightly dangerous parts of Norrath. These orcs were no deathfist scouts, they were mean, some even took on skills of the rogue trade. Some were intelligent enough to form bands, guilds if you will. Dark struck one down that was of the Wicked Crown.<br>
<br>
During his stay in Highpass, Darkrayne was approached by a Half Elf speaking so fast her words came out as gibberish. <br>
She was asking of his skills it turned out. But not those of being a healer, those of what his reputation had grown to be.<br>
About a week ago, the Half Elf was with her newly wed husband when they were attacked by a Griffin in the Karanas.<br>
The Half Elf's husband sacrificed himself for her to get away.<br>
She ran here to Highpass where she heard of a being that could just speak a word and his foe would fall. She now sought after him, to not save her husband as he would by now be griffin waste, but for Darkrayne to kill said monster.<br>
The Half Elf also said something about this Griffin to be legendary as well and needed a legendary hero to defeat it.<br>
&quot;Grim Feather ate my husband, please...help me put my husbands soul to rest.&quot; Darkrayne laughed once, but the look she gave him meant she was serious. &quot;I prayed to Tunare that she would send you to my aid, please! I beg you do this for me&quot;<br>
<br>
After a pause Darkrayne spoke, &quot;You approach me, claiming a message from your goddess? AND you ask me to do something in HER name? Were you not serious, I would almost have to....I must tell you now, I am no hero, and ESPECIALLY not the servant of that being you mentioned. It is folly for one such as you or I to mess with beings so great as is Grim Feather.&quot; Darkrayne was interrupted, &quot;But...the stories about you, they say you can strike any foe down with just one word&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, if the one word summons my magic and strikes an already weakened being down yes, just the one is all that's necessary.&quot; Darkrayne smiles evilly &quot;But...the stories&quot; Darkrayne interrupted her &quot;Are just that, stories.&quot;<br>
&quot;And my husband's death?&quot; The half elf spoke<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, if you have any remains of him, i could attempt to ressurect him..don't know how clean he will be, might be a bit smelly too.&quot; <br>
&quot;HE WAS EATEN WHOLE&quot; the Elf protested<br>
<br>
&quot;Then that would make for remains tough to come by wouldn't it?&quot;<br>
<br>
The follower of Tunare sadly departed his presence. <br>
<br>
Darkrayne walked into Highkeep to visit a certain banker.<br>
